HEADWORD: Shalloon
<hw>Shal*loon"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>chalon</ets>, from <ets>Ch⟦acir⟧lons</ets>, in France, where it was
first made.]</ety> <def>A thin, loosely woven, twilled worsted
stuff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In blue <qex>shalloon</qex> shall Hannibal be clad.</q>
